ce in the writings of major eighteenth-century thinkers including Locke, Addison, Burke, and Kant. This new take on an old story ultimately challenges readers to reconsider form and why it matters.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Aesthetics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishz978311070482208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110704648oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2020z978311069231040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300255713423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300255713.jpg  a978-3-11-069231-0  YUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070482-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DPHb2020